snippet.textDisplay:
I'd be worried if you didn't change. A big part of becoming an adult is growing into yourself. You're just at a stage where you need to take control of your life and look ahead.

I used to be very high maintenance from age 14 to 19. Life hit me with illness and other events, and I went from two hours worth of glammed up EVERY day to not wearing makeup for weeks. I was put on a completely different path and people were judging me for it. But trust me when I say keep moving forwards. You'll find so many more valuable things in life. Accept, but don't carry your past. Find happiness in the present.
